Total IP Control v1.1.2 - Release Notes
Copyright (c) 2026 Sysop Network

Thank you for installing Total IP Control, centralized IP management,
proxy detection, connection control, and audit logging for The Major
BBS v10.

What's new in this release:
  * New GeoIP provider: ipinfo.io. Select IPINFO.IO in the Provider
    field on the GeoIP Location screen. ipinfo derives its city and
    region data from its own network probing rather than reselling a
    shared free database, so it is typically more accurate at the city
    level than the other providers.
  * ipinfo requires a free API token, one per sysop. Sign up for a free
    account at https://ipinfo.io/signup, copy the token from your
    account dashboard, and paste it into the existing Key field on the
    GeoIP Location screen. The free tier allows 50,000 lookups per
    month, far more than a BBS needs.

  * New State format option on the GeoIP Location screen: CODE or FULL.
    CODE shows the two-letter state code (Minnesota becomes MN); FULL
    shows the full name. It mirrors the existing Country format option
    and defaults to CODE.
  * The API Host field is now optional. Leave it blank and the correct
    host for the selected provider is used automatically; only fill it
    in to point a provider at a custom endpoint.

Notes:
  * By default US states are shown using the two-letter code (for
    example Minnesota is shown as MN), matching the other providers; set
    State format to FULL for the full name. Non-US regions always keep
    their full name (for example London, England, GB).
  * ipinfo returns the country as a two-letter code only; Total IP
    Control maps it to a full country name, so the Country format
    (full/code) option works with ipinfo just like the other providers.

Installing:
  1. Copy SNTIPCTL.DLL, SNTIPCTL.MDF, and SNTIPCTL.MSG into your BBS
     installation directory (typically C:\BBSV10).
  2. Restart the BBS. Total IP Control prints its version and active
     feature set to the startup log.
  3. Sign on as a user holding the MASTER key and run /TOTALIP to
     configure the module. All features are off by default.

Upgrading from an earlier version:
  1. Stop the BBS.
  2. Replace SNTIPCTL.DLL, SNTIPCTL.MDF, and SNTIPCTL.MSG with the
     files from this package.
  3. Restart the BBS. Your existing settings are preserved; no
     reconfiguration is required.

  If you are replacing the older PROXCLIP or IPControl modules, remove
  their entries from wgserv.cfg.

Notes for this upgrade:
  * There is no settings-file change in this release. The provider
    selection is stored in the existing settings record, so upgrading
    is drop-in.
  * To try the new provider, open the GeoIP Location screen, set
    Provider to IPINFO.IO, and enter your free ipinfo token in the Key
    field.

